      "content": "That's a good start for the tone. It definitely captures that sense of defensiveness. To make it even more visceral for the reader, I want to lean into the more intense social tensions. Could you write a follow-up to that conversation where they get a bit more specific and heated about why they view the activists as a threat? I want to capture the actual language and the deeper, more ingrained fears they had—the kind of stuff that wouldn't be in a polite history textbook, but was definitely being said in private rooms like this. Make it feel gritty and unvarnished.",
